Kungawa Mazembe was last seen while playing outside his family home in Melkbos Street in Laingville on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - Saint Helena Bay police have requested the public's help in their search for a missing four-year-old boy. Kungawa Mazembe was last seen while playing outside his family home in Melkbos Street in Laingville on Tuesday. The little boy was wearing a blue track top, jeans and grey rain boots when he disappeared. Anyone with information can contact the SAPS or The Pink Ladies Organisation.